news.title: Mittal Builders, HoABL to invest ₹2,000 crore on 11-acre project in Mumbai region
news.para: Mittal Builders partners with House of Abhinandan Lodha for a housing project. The project is in the Mumbai Metropolitan Region. Investment is estimated at Rs 2,000 crore. The project will span 11 acres.

news.title: Ludhiana officials cancel allotment of 70 shops in Jainpur village
news.para: In Ludhiana, allotment of 70 shops got cancelled. The reason was forged procedures and low rental rates. The shops were near Ladhowal bypass. Officials are investigating the matter. A fresh allotment process will start soon.

news.title: Delhi civic body likely to install rooftop solar panels on 989 buildings to cut power costs
news.para: The Municipal Corporation of Delhi plans to install rooftop solar plants. The project aims to reduce reliance on conventional power. It will cover nearly a thousand buildings. This initiative supports India's clean energy goals.

news.title: Only 15 out of 8,000 villagers opt for land pooling in Mohali, farmers protest Gmada policy
news.para: Gmada's land pooling initiative in Mohali encounters significant opposition. Only a handful of landowners have opted in. Farmers protest against the proposed land acquisition. They claim inadequate compensation and fear displacement. The scheme aims to curb unauthorized colonies.

news.title: Ludhiana civic body struggles to implement UID number plates for households over drone issues
news.para: Ludhiana's ambitious project to assign unique identification number plates to households faces its third relaunch after two previous attempts failed due to execution delays and contractor disputes. The latest effort, backed by the World Bank, aims to digitize property records and improve revenue collection.

news.title: Puravankara to jointly develop 5.5-acre land in East Bengaluru
news.para: Puravankara Group will jointly develop a 5.5-acre land in Balagere, East Bengaluru. The project has an estimated gross development value exceeding ₹1,000 crore. It offers a saleable area of 0.83 million sq ft. The company expects to launch the project within the next six to nine months.

news.title: Asian Paints exits Akzo Nobel India; sells 4.42% stake for ₹734 crore
news.para: Asian Paints has sold its entire 4.42 percent stake in Akzo Nobel India for Rs 734 crore. The sale was executed through an open market transaction. Sajjan Jindal's JSW Paints had announced acquiring Akzo Nobel's India unit. ICICI Prudential Mutual Fund and Eastspring Investments India purchased shares of Akzo Nobel India.

news.title: Karnataka government plans special cell to recover dues from builders
news.para: Karnataka is establishing a dedicated 'Recovery Cell' to enforce K-Rera orders and ensure real estate developers compensate homebuyers. This action addresses the non-compliance of builders who previously ignored Rera directives. As of May 31, 2025, over Rs 724 crore is due from builders, with Bengaluru urban accounting for Rs 710 crore.

news.title: Valor emerges as top bidder for Lavasa with ₹771-crore offer
news.para: Valor Estate, formerly DB Realty, has emerged as the highest bidder for Lavasa Corporation, offering ₹771.09 crore. The selection followed a competitive bidding process with ten rounds, but the deal hinges on environmental clearances, a crucial factor for lenders wary of past experiences. The committee of creditors will negotiate further and decide on the next steps.

news.title: Maharashtra government to legalize subdivided land parcels up to January 1, 2025
news.para: The Maharashtra government will legalize subdivided land parcels up to January 1, 2025, by relaxing land fragmentation laws, benefiting over 50 lakh families. Plots up to one guntha formed before the deadline will be considered legal, granting property rights. A detailed SOP will be finalized within 15 days to address layout approvals and land registration.

news.title: Logan Group wins bondholder approval for Shenzen unit's debt restructuring
news.para: Shenzhen-based Logan Group has secured bondholder approval for a comprehensive debt restructuring, encompassing 21 onshore bonds issued by Shenzhen Logan Holdings. The restructuring offers bondholders options like asset conversion, debt swaps, cash repurchase, or equity economic rights.

news.title: Bank of England relaxes mortgage lending rules to help boost growth
news.para: Bank of England will permit British banks to issue riskier mortgages. This move aims to support the government's initiative to increase home ownership. Individual lenders can now exceed loan-to-income limits. The overall sector will still have a 15% cap on high loan-to-income lending. This change could result in approximately 36,000 new higher loan-to-income mortgages annually.

news.title: Smartworks raises ₹173.64 crore from anchor investors ahead of IPO
news.para: Smartworks Coworking Spaces has secured Rs 173.64 crore from anchor investors prior to its IPO, allocating shares to domestic mutual funds like Tata Mutual Fund and Baroda BNP Paribas. The IPO, opening on July 10, aims to raise nearly Rs 600 crore for business expansion and debt reduction.

news.title: UK builders to pay $136 million to housing programmes after competition probe
news.para: Following a Competition and Markets Authority (CMA) investigation into potential anticompetitive conduct, seven major UK housebuilders, including Barratt Redrow and Taylor Wimpey, have committed to providing £100 million to affordable housing initiatives.

news.title: Hong Kong's Henderson Land to raise $1 billion through convertible bonds
news.para: Henderson Land Development in Hong Kong plans to raise funds through convertible bonds. The aim is to secure HK$8 billion for business growth and debt management. The initial conversion price is HK$36 per share.

news.title: Manglam Group & The Fern Hotels join forces for a serviced apart’otel in Jaipur
news.para: Manglam Group is set to develop a new serviced apart’otel in Jaipur. The property will be part of the Pinkwalk mixed-use development. Pinkwalk will feature commercial and studio spaces. The Group plans to expand its hospitality footprint.

news.title: Prestige Estates reports ₹12,126 crore worth of sales in Q1 FY26
news.para: Prestige Estates Projects witnessed a remarkable surge in Q1 FY26, with sales soaring to ₹12,126 crore, a four-fold increase year-on-year, driven primarily by strong performance in the NCR region. The company sold 4,718 units across 9.55 million sq ft, while also consolidating its stakes in two real estate arms for ₹325 crore, strengthening its portfolio and market position.

news.title: Madras HC imposes ₹1 lakh cost on GCC commissioner for inaction over unauthorized construction
news.para: Madras High Court has levied a ₹1 lakh fine on Greater Chennai Corporation (GCC) Commissioner J Kumaragurubaran due to inaction regarding unauthorized construction in Royapuram zone.

news.title: Lucknow civic body gets charge of four sectors of Gomtinagar Extension
news.para: Gomtinagar Extension residents can anticipate improved civic amenities as the Lucknow Development Authority (LDA) has transferred maintenance of Sectors 1, 4, 5, and 6 to the Lucknow Municipal Corporation (LMC).

news.title: Task force to fire-audit all commercial buildings, malls in Kolkata
news.para: Kolkata's fire safety measures are set to get a major boost. The state task force will broaden its audit scope. It will now include all commercial buildings, malls, hospitals, and schools. The focus is on improving water sourcing for firefighting. Electric meter placement and fire license renewals will also be stricter. Ninety-two waterspouts are identified across 144 wards.
